'''Otto Nietzche''' (20 November 1969 - 24 April 2024) was a German politician, museum worker and soldier who served as the director of the Cologne School Board from 1995 to 2003. He is best known for his ambitious but unsuccessful attempts to run for high political offices, such as the governorship of his home state and the Chancellorship of the country. 

==Early life==
Otto was born in Cologne, Germany to jeweler Lara Klum (1935 - 2023) and hairdresser Nicholas "Nick" Nietzche (1934 - 2016). He had two siblings, Friedrich (born 1964), a hairdresser like his father, and Hannah (born 1974), a flight attendant. He also has a stepbrother named Liam from his mother's brief marriage to retired restaurant worker Kilian Becker (1944 - 2018). He had a pet mongrel named Marlon (1965 - 1979).

