==Personal life==
Nietzche met his future wife, grocer Pauline Zimmer (born 1969) at age ten. They dated for ten years throughout their school years and got married in 1989 during Otto's third year in the military. They had four children and five grandchildren together: 
* Sofia (born 1989) - Navy sailor 
* Lothar (born 1994) - Receptionist for Swift Counseling 
* Annabell (born 1996) - Firefighter 
* Lara (born 2011)

==Death==
Otto died of a heart attack on 24 April 2024 at the age of 54. He is survived by his wife, four children, five grandchildren and three siblings. His gravestone is marked with his medal of honor. 

